    "name": "Berkut",
    "epitet": "Purgatorial Prince",
    "display": "Berkut: Purgatorial Prince",
    "description": "Heir presumptive to the Rigelian throne. Fell into a deep despair when the truth about Alm came out. Gave his betrothed's life to Duma to obtain power. Appears in Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia.",
    "artist": "Asatani Tomoyo (麻谷知世)",
    "voiceActorEN": "Ian Sinclair",
    "voiceActorJP": "鈴木達央＆銀河万丈",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "Hah! I am Berkut! I shall end all things...with Duma's supreme power!",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "All this time! All the effort! What has it all been for?! Tell me, Uncle... Duma... Someone...TELL ME!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "You ask me of my...home? I have nothing of the sort. Even Rigel is now forever beyond my grasp...",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Ah, the summoner-savior... Tell me, do you see the strings commanding you to dance to liars' songs?",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "If you thirst for power, give all you are to Duma. Your love, your hate, your past—everything!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Have you seen Rinea? I'm looking for her... Rinea! Where have you gone?! Please, answer me...",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "So, you are <Player Name>? You will be sacrificed to Duma, as <Friend Name> commands.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "Hah! Very good... This can only be a blessing from Duma!",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Bow before Duma's power!",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Have...even the gods forsaken me?!",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Show me the enemy. I will use my new power to eradicate them!",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "You, summoner...how pitiful you are. To the people of this world, you are little more than a walking sacrifice. They praise you as a savior, but once your usefulness has run its course, they will cast you aside... Of course, you struggle with the idea. You want to tell me how wrong I am. Your naivety is plain on your face. You see only the surface of things. Beneath, the world is cruel—everyone hides their true intentions. Someday, you will realize the truth as I have... When that day comes, I will relish the regret on your face... Hah!",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
